With the obvious exceptions of the bare gravitational constant  and the square of the bare mass  all other 
couplings in  are characterised by the absence of mass dimensions at . 
Moreover, the interaction between surface and volume terms, renders, effectively, the extrinsic curvature  of the manifold's boundary as yet another coupling in the theory. 
In the context of both dimensional regularisation - which manifests all divergences as poles in  at the dimensional limit  after an analytical extension of  - and minimal subtraction - which is characterised by the absence of finite parts in the counterterms at  - the expansions of the bare parameters in the scalar action in powers of the poles and of the scalar self-coupling  are 












































