The semi-classical mass parameter m is, generally, a free parameter. In view of the absence of mass at
semi-classical level in the present theory the parameter m refers, evidently, to the order at which the 
mass is possibly generated through vacuum effects. It will be shown that to  there is no
mass generation in the theory and the speculation herein is that it is absent to all orders. As stated, 
in what follows the regulating scheme will be predicated on an analytical extension of the covering 
manifold's dimensionality to an arbitrary value . Such an approach is preferable as it preserves the 
maximal symmetry which underlies the method of images. However, the formal extension of  to 
topologically flat dimensions such as  as opposed to  will have no impact on
the renormalisation group behaviour of the theory and it is expected, in addition to leave its 
pole-structure intact. In addition, consistency with the renormalisation group behaviour of 
the theory necessitates that the coupling in the conformal sector at semi-classical level be taken, in 
(1), (3) and (6c), at its -dimensional value of  instead of at its 
four-dimensional value of .

